mts.s: Furthermore having continuously updated content will help to keep long-lasting relationship with the customers.

I. Home Page - pretty obvious, although there are a lot of options as far
as content - fitness articles, member profiles (might be kinda hard for
now), ect. This would be a good place to have RSS feeds on the side: WOD's
twitter, ect. Once we have an idea of the kind of content you want users
to see when they first see the site, we can start designing the page
layout. We can easily implement the same kind of bar menu that is used on
all of the sites you sent me. The pages we fill this bar with are up to
you, and depend on how much content you want to put on the website. The
following three are on all of the sites you sent me:

II. About Us - A description of your gym specifically and its goals.
Pretty straightforward.

III. What is Crossfit? - A general description of the Crossfit program.
Some sites like CrossfitLA go into great detail, while others just provide
a few paragraphs and links to the general crossfit site.

IV. Contact us - A page specifically devoted to just having the Gym's
address, email address, and links to other social media sites. It would
also be cool to use the Google Maps API like on the Marietta website.
Our development team must elicit requirements from Paul to create a website that effectively addresses his business’s needs.
